  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      E-Transportation is increasing all over the world. It is not known if the used engines
      interfere with cardiac implantable electronic devices. The study evaluates such potential
      interferences in vivo.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      E-Transportation is increasing all over the world. It is not known if the used engines
      interfere with cardiac implantable electronic devices. The study evaluates different types of
      electric motors with regard to electromagnetic interference with implanted pacemakers or
      cardioverter-defibrillators.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
